William Frederick Koch the doctor who cured cancer in the 40s and got exiled to Brazil by the FDA over it suspected that electron donor "tryptophan derivatives" interfered with cellular respiration. This was before serotonin was isolated so he was basically predicting its effects

Estrogens and prolactin are also electron donors. He saw quinones as the opposite of that because they are electron acceptors and thought viruses also worked the same way as serotonin. Sort of explains how Cyproheptadine type drugs are both anti-serotonergic and also anti-virals.
